# Zombie rules

See `docs/PROTECTED_SYSTEMS.md` (Zombie movement, OOB authority).

## Protected

- `Zombie._check_out_of_bounds()` is the **sole** authoritative fall/OOB death path.
- Zombie movement and `_apply_anti_clump_nudge` are protected — do not tune while doing map/visual/tooling tasks.
- Per-map bounds come from `RaceMapDefinition` applied via `RaceMapController` → `ZombieConfig`.

## Banned unless explicitly requested

- Map-specific branches or hardcoded coordinates in `zombie.gd`.
- Re-enabling map void kill zones as authoritative.
- Changing movement/OOB while building unrelated features.

## Death causes

Use `fell` (below `out_of_bounds_min_y`) and `out_of_bounds` (lateral X/Z) distinctly — see `docs/TESTING.md`.

## Tests

Any change to `zombie.gd` locomotion, OOB, or anti-clump: `--tier=smoke` + `--tier=core` (`void_oob_authority_test.gd`).
